# Project Layout

## Architecture (refactor postвЂ“v1.5)

- **`SimEngine`** (`game/sim_engine.py`) вЂ” pure simulation: world, systems, entities for the running match, `update()`, `get_game_state()`, `build_snapshot()` into a read-only **`SimStateSnapshot`** (`game/sim/snapshot.py`).
- **`GameEngine`** (`game/engine.py`) вЂ” presentation orchestration (the refactorвЂ™s **PresentationLayer** role; the class name stayed `GameEngine` for compatibility). It owns pygame init (when not headless), camera, **HUD/panels/menus**, audio, VFX, and composes `self.sim: SimEngine`. The pygame **world/entity** draw path delegates to **`PygameRenderer`** using the snapshot; HUD and chrome stay here.
- **`InputHandler`** uses **`GameCommands`** (`game/game_commands.py`), not a raw `GameEngine` type вЂ” default wiring is `EngineBackedGameCommands`.
- **2D / pygame** вЂ” `game/graphics/pygame_renderer.py` consumes `SimStateSnapshot` per frame for terrain в†’ units в†’ fog-style pipeline (see `GameEngine` and `docs/refactor/engine_access_inventory.md`).
- **3D / Ursina** вЂ” `game/graphics/ursina_app.py` runs the windowed loop; `game/graphics/ursina_renderer.py` renders from snapshots (engine bridge access tracked in `docs/refactor/engine_access_inventory.md`).
- **Full refactor map & stages:** `.cursor/plans/master_plan_architecture_refactor.md`

